org.safs.model.annotations

Annotation Type JSAFSTest


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface JSAFSTest
    Tags a method as one that can be automatically executed by an appropriate Driver test runner looking for such annotations.

    Any test runner finding such methods might also check for the InjectJSAFS annotation provided an appropriate driver for use by the Class.

    Author:
    Carl Nagle OCT 15, 2013
    See Also:
    InjectJSAFS, JSAFSBefore, JSAFSAfter, Utilities.autoConfigure(String, JSAFSConfiguredClassStore)

    • Element Detail

      • Description

        public abstract java.lang.String Description
        Default:
        "JSAFSTest"

      • Order

        public abstract int Order
        Lower order will be executed before higher order tests. Tests of the same order value are not guaranteed to execute in any specific order and may even be intentionally randomized. The default is 1000.
        Returns:
        'order' determines in what order tests shall be executed.
        Default:
        1000

      • value

        public abstract int value
        A default for Order not requiring Order= prefix. The default is 1000.
        Returns:
        'order' determines in what order tests shall be executed.
        Default:
        1000

      • Name

        public abstract java.lang.String Name
        Descriptive unique Name for this test used in logging and reporting.
        Returns:
        String. If an empty String (default) then the Method name might be used.
        Default:
        ""

      • Summary

        public abstract boolean Summary
        Used to indicate test summary information should be output to the log at the completion of this method execution. Default is false. The user must add Summary=true if they want the summary to appear in the log for this testcase.
        Returns:
        Default:
        false
